						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have a toon that I've done some alchemy on. Some suggestions that I could give would be as an aspiring alchemist, there are many things you can make to get your chemistry skills up and these same items are used by alot of other crafters. For instance, when you scribe your artisan essentials volume 3 book you will have recipes for Chloro Wash, Chloro Resin and Chloro Oil. Also you will have Fossil Temper. Alchemists are the people that crafters come to for all of the types of washes, resins, oils and tempers. Tempers are used in forging things like bars of metal, weapons, armor, etc. Washes, Resins and Oils are used in tailoring items, craftsmen need certain ones to make their wares as well. And alchemists also get the ability to make Inks for the scholar types to make spells and abilities.
<br />

<br />
So you too can make spells while you level up. And heres a bit of information not a whole lot of people are aware of yet. Once a Scholar hits level 20, they become a jeweler, sage or alchemist. Sages make the priest and mage type spells. Jewelers make the scout type abilities and Alchemists make the Warrior type abilites. You can make Apprentice IV ones on pristine quality combines using the normal inks. With rare inks you can make Adept III of these spells using the correct recipes.
<br />

<br />
And as for leveling up your artisan, one good thing to do is when you gain a level, look at your new recipes to see what new items you can make. The higher the level of recipe you make, the faster you will gain levels. And at the beginning stages of crafting, it isn't hard to gain a few level in a small amount of time.
<br />

<br />
Also as an Alchemist you will be able to make things such as potions and poisons. They have a wide range of effects. My alchemist is only level 24 and I have allready seen recipes that I can make for potions and poisons that can heal the user, buffs the user, puts a damage shield on the user, or even casts a damage over time spell on the enemy or just plain debuffs the mob. Many different variations.<br />_________________<br />Aaldyin
<br />
Officer of <a href="http://www.forgottenevil.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Forgotten Evil</a>
<br />
Mistmoore Server</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
