&nbsp; &nbsp; * paraffin wax candle&#40;1&#41;
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
-----------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
I recommend making at least 20 Inks/session (making more than 20 can be a little too tedious). You should get some good XP and have enough ink to "p-lvl" a few lvls.
<br />

<br />
Now that you have your inks, "pristine"(or produce an apprentice VI) every even-conned spell on your list. If you lvl, buy the next lvl's book and start on those even con spells.
<br />

<br />
You will receive a SWEET xp bonus for every recipe you pristine (for the first time/recipe). And at lvl 20, you will be given some +durability skills, making the "pristining process" much easier.... (after lvl 20 if you can't pristine everything in your book, first try, then you are either very unlucky or you need to read more crafting guides.)[/code]<br />_________________<br />&gt;&gt;----------------------}&gt;
<br />
Youkai ~ Lucan D'Lere
<br />
29th lvl Assassinator
